Nov 17 2009 	Dated and feels worn	I've stayed at this place over the years and liked in the past, This is the first visit in about 4 years and this time, the property feels dated. It needs a good renovation. It's functional but less than what you'd expect from a Crowne Plaza. There is a small mall nearby and you can get some restaurants at the next block, but unless you take a taxi or have someone drive you, it's not really a good location (unless you are visiting the Olympic Green, which is within easy walking distance)The breakfast buffet is OK and the day that I ate there, it was packed and the service was poor. It took 3 or 4 reminders and more than 10 minutes for them to bring new bowls out. They took the plates away quick enough but refill of coffee was slow. It still bothers me that people can smoke in the lobby. Some of the other hotels seem to not have that problem.	
Nov 16 2009 	Cold and comfortable what you'd expect from a 4/5 star business hotel	I stayed here towards the end of September for 4 nights. It's everything I'd expected from this class of a hotel. Comfortable, but impersonal hotel. The rooms are quite spacious and very comfortable. I had a corporate rate which included internet use, so I didn't feel the pinch of the pay-per-use internet users which I read in other reviews.The lobby is very large but had the stench of cigarettes since smoking is allowed there. Quite a number of very nice looking restaurants in the lobby but I didn't try any of them. My room was facing the courtyard (and 4th Ring road, I think), so it was a little bit noisy as they were having their Oktoberfest promotion in the tents on the ground floor. The loud music was bothering me slightly, but that's also because I'm a light sleeper and like things absolutely silent.Next door to the hotel is a small mall with a supermarket, some specialty shops as well as a food court. The food court was pretty good with very affordable prices and a variety of local food. I enjoyed eating there a number of times. It was good that I didn't have to eat in the hotel restaurants all the time, with the food court right next door available for light and simple meals.Across the road, about 10-15 minutes walk is also the Olympic park where the Birds Nest stadium and Watercube swimming arena is. It was quite a treat to be able to just walk there and see these amazing architectural marvels.The area is generally quite safe and I spent one night walking around. Some spots were quite dark but I didn't feel threatened at any time. Taxis are also readily available at the hotel.Overall, it was one of those forgettable stays when traveling for business, which is not necessarily a bad thing because the memorable ones (for business travel) are usually the ones where something bad happened! Would I stay here again? Yes, because there are no surprises and everything is as expected.	
