Aug 27 2009	Beijing Crown Plaza OK stay expensive Internet	Our large group of 30 people for this company paid trip went to Beijing for 5 days, this is the hotel our travel agency put us in. The hotel itself is clean, and very nicely done. I don't know the price we got, since we got this as a packaged deal. The place is a bit far from the main city center, 30 minutes or so none traffic, but it is about 5-10 minutes walk from the 2009 Olympic Park. The place is very quiet as well, since most places around closes after 10pm. There are some small stores and restaurants around but closes after 10pm as well. Overall, I am satisified with the stay. However, if you do need internet, this trip will be expensive for you. There is NO free internet in the rooms, so you will have to pay for depending on the time you needed. There is also a business center in the 2nd floor with both English or Chinese computers that you can use as well. They can also rent out laptop/copier/fax etc if you need to. From my understanding, they do speak some English if you speak slow. Oh, the pool area also closes around 10pm, but at 9:30pm, they will not let you in anymore to use it. While we were there, very very few people used the pool, but it was very clean and quiet. The hotel gym is also very nice and clean if you decided to use it. They do have some yoga/pilate supplies if you want to use as well. Their breakfast was ok, not the best, especially when they have lots of people then they are not able bring out much variety of food. Also, we asked them to fill our water bottle, it took them about 5 minutes just to do so, so you may want to buy your water elsewhere instead. They do give 1 free bottle of water per person each day left in your room. Finally, their water is very hard water, so it made washing my hair not so pleasant experience. The last time I stayed in a Shanghai hotel I did not have this problem.	
