Mar 12 2009 	Overall good	I stayed here 10 days for business. Compared to other Crowne Plazas the service was maybe not just up to scratch. My main complaint is that Internet access is expensive in the rooms (£12 for every 24 hours) and WLAN in the cafes/bars of the hotel is not so comfortable, and the cost of drinks you are expected to buy is high. You can sit in the lobby and access WLAN but there are not many seats. On the positive side, Internet access is made so easy.Note that 15% service charge is added on to every part of the hotel bill.During my stay the gym/pool was uder renovation, so as from March 2009 this facility should be up and running again, and pretty good. A new small shopping mall is open under the North Times Tower - only 50 metres from the main door. Here you can visit Zoe's bar who provide very nice coffee and cakes at fair prices with free WLAN access.The concierge were helpful but overall the problem is a language one.The location of the hotel is perfect from the point of view of the Birds Nest stadium and the Water Cube which you can visit about 50 RMBs each.Shopping needs a nerve with haggling and the Clothing Market can be recommended, but remember all products are probably 'seconds'. Use the subway (1.5km from hotel) and get anywhere for 2 RMBs a stretch. (Airport express is 25RMBs.)Trips are organised by the hotel. 470 RMBs to visit the Great Wall, which is a must, even if probably overpriced.	
Oct 16 2008 	Nice but with problems...	We spent 6 nights at this hotel, and were not too impressed with it. First of all, we were given two twin beds, and the staff was unable to find a king/queen bed room for us, even though we stayed for a 6 nights, which is a pretty long stay. They had rooms available with a queen bed, but at a higher rate, and were unwilling to give us (since we were unwilling to pay extra!). Second, unless you're into the Olympic village, which is right next to the hotel, the location is not convenient, the hotel is pretty far out, there's not much around it, and you need to take a taxi or the subway (which is 15 minutes away) to go to the attractions. Third, I needed to get train tickets to go to Shanghai, and most hotels can buy tickets for you for a small fee, well, this upscale, expensive hotel, has a travel center that would arrange only airplane tickets (at a crazy price) with a staffer who didn't speak English, no train tickets. So they ended up sending me to the post office to get my train tickets which was complicated given that I don't speak Chinese. Considering that the post office is close to the hotel, and that they have plenty of staff, and that all hotels provide train tickets, it's appalling that this pretentious hotel wouldn't help guests with such a common request, simply ridiculous! Fourth, the rate was way too high for what we got: 1,800RMB/night with only one breakfast. Given the location, and service provided. Fifth, there were some problems with the rate they initially quoted us, and with a breakfast we were overcharged for, and when we were checking out it took one hour to solve these simple issues. The nice things about this hotel are the clean, comfortable rooms, some staff speaks pretty good English, and most of all a very nice (albeit expensive, 170rmb per person!) breakfast. But overall, I wouldn't recommend it for tourists, too far out, too expensive for what you get, no help for train tickets.	
